name: Chicago Food Map 11" x 22"
description: Limited edition giclée print of 'Chicago Food Map' by Joe Mills During my two year stay in Australia, I found many of my drawings and sketches focused on my hometown of Chicago. This illustration was researched thoroughly in order to represent the tremendous diversity of Chicago's cuisine from every corner of the city. From restaurants with Michelin stars to neighborhood establishments to holes in the wall to the variety of ethnic cuisines, this print embraces all that is great about eating out in Chicago. Each restaurant included is organized on this illustration by their location. While not every great eatery could be included, the chosen restaurants are considered by many to be some of the best places to eat in Chicago.
